The Inspector-General of Police, Mohammed Adamu, has announced the disbandment of the Special Anti-Robbery Squad (SARS) of the Nigeria Police Force. Adamu announced this in a live broadcast on Sunday. Daily Times reports that the IGP made the announcement after days of online and offline protests against the brutality and extra-judicial killings by SARS operatives nationwide. READ ALSO: 2021 Budget: N336m allocated for anti-hate speech, fake news campaign Many Nigerians and even some international celebrities who joined the protest, have been protesting against the end of SARS. Details laterâ€¦